<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10093] Invalid internal query for static compact tables</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10093</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When dealing with static compact table on the CQL side and we do a &lt;tt&gt;SELECT * FROM table;&lt;/tt&gt; query, we generate the wrong clustering filter. More precisely, we create a name query that selects the &lt;tt&gt;EMPTY&lt;/tt&gt; clustering, but that&apos;s an invalid clustering since static compact table have 1 clustering column (internally at least). What we really want to query is the static parts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is the reason for the failure of some dtests (&lt;tt&gt;bootstrap_test:TestBootstrap.read_from_bootstrapped_node_test&lt;/tt&gt; for instance). More precisely, the invalid filter created breaks serialization, which is why this is only really a problem on multi-node tests.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
